  "title": "Accessing Shared Network Drives and File Shares",
  "question": "How do I access shared network drives and file shares?",
  "answer": "Windows: Step 1 - Click on the 'File Explorer' icon on your taskbar. Step 2 - In the left sidebar, select 'This PC'. Step 3 - Click on 'Computer' in the top menu, then select 'Map network drive'. Step 4 - Choose a drive letter and enter the folder path (e.g., \\server\sharedfolder) in the 'Folder' field. Step 5 - Check 'Reconnect at sign-in' if you want to access it automatically in the future, then click 'Finish'. macOS: Step 1 - Open 'Finder' from your dock. Step 2 - In the menu bar, click 'Go', then select 'Connect to Server'. Step 3 - Enter the server address (e.g., smb://server/sharedfolder) in the 'Server Address' field. Step 4 - Click 'Connect', and if prompted, enter your network credentials (username and password). Step 5 - Once connected, the shared drive will appear on your desktop and in the Finder sidebar for easy access."
}
